{
  "description": {
    "title": "Full-stack showcase - banking equilibrium + K-MSR decree + auction-reserve floor + CBAM + sectors (small/fast)",
    "purpose": "pe.command demo model exercising one block from every major category in a single 4-year, 3-participant scenario that solves in ~2 s. Feature manifest: core + banking + msr + price_controls + cbam (sector pools are config-level pass-through - the manifest cannot see them by design, see ets/blocks/manifest.py docstring).",
    "composition": "Rubin/Schennach banking equilibrium is the price-formation hub (r = 5.5%, initial aggregate bank 10 Mt, relaxed no-arbitrage). Supply operators compose INSIDE the solver's fixed point and read only lagged state: the K-MSR decree (hybrid mode, price band 4,000-5,100 KRW, max intake/release 5 Mt, pre-funded reserve 6 Mt) reads the PREVIOUS year's solved price; the auction-reserve floor (4,200 -> 4,500 KRW) clips delivered prices LAST. CBAM is a post-clearing reporting overlay (F6): EUA reference 110,000 -> 140,000 KRW vs domestic KAU prices - no feedback into clearing. Sector pools (Power/Steel/Petrochemical) derive each participant's free allocation and the auction volume from per-sector cap and auction-share trajectories.",
    "inputs": "Sector caps 55/30/15 -> 46/26/13 Mt (total 100 -> 85); auction shares Power 0.60 -> 0.75, industry 0.05 -> 0.12; linear MACs 900/1400/1800 KRW per Mt; BAU 108 -> 97.5 Mt; POSCO exports 30% into CBAM scope, LG 15%.",
    "expected_output": {
      "Equilibrium Carbon Price (2026-2029)": [
        4200.0,
        4300.0,
        4400.0,
        4500.0
      ],
      "Unsold Allowances (2026-2029)": [
        2.0,
        0.738,
        0.0,
        0.0
      ],
      "MSR Withheld (2026-2029)": [
        0.0,
        5.0,
        0.0,
        0.0
      ],
      "MSR Reserve Pool (2026-2029)": [
        6.0,
        11.0,
        11.0,
        11.0
      ],
      "Total CBAM Liability (2026, KRW x Mt)": 1137350.0,
      "reading": "The floor binds across the horizon (delivered price = floor path). The decree is neutral in 2026 (first year has no lagged signal), takes in 5 Mt in 2027 because the lagged 2026 market-clearing price sits below the 4,000 KRW band floor, and is in-band neutral afterwards; the intake shrinks 2027 unsold volume from ~2 Mt to 0.74 Mt. CBAM liability grows with the widening EUA-KAU gap and is diagnostics-only."
    },
    "run": "PYTHONPATH=src .venv/bin/python -m ets.cli --config examples/showcase_full_stack.json"
  },
